MATCH_TOOL: Write
MATCH_PATTERN: docs/reports/pulse-mockups/.*\.html
ADVISORY: |
  Pulse mockup conventions (implicit — follow existing files):

  1. Numbered incrementally. Name as `NN-topic.html` using the next integer after
     the highest existing number. Files 01-11 already exist.

  2. Serve locally via a background shell:
       cd docs/reports/pulse-mockups && python3 -m http.server 8765
       (use Bash run_in_background=true; kill at end of session)
     Share URL as http://localhost:8765/NN-topic.html

  3. Styling vocabulary. Inherit from 11-cast-strip-v2.html (newest) or
     08-full-interaction-prototype.html (original). Palette lives in `:root`
     CSS variables (--bg #0a0a0e, --surface #13131a, --accent #ff3b6f,
     --gold #ffd700, --online #2ecc71, --whisper #9b59b6, etc). Font:
     `Outfit` via Google Fonts. Phone frame: 390px wide, ~780-820px tall,
     rounded 36px border, dark phone chrome.

  4. Persona images live on the staging CDN:
       https://staging-assets.peckingorder.ca/personas/persona-XX/headshot.png
       https://staging-assets.peckingorder.ca/personas/persona-XX/medium.png
       https://staging-assets.peckingorder.ca/personas/persona-XX/full.png
     Use `medium` for social panel hero thumbs, `full` for the DM hero gallery
     max, `headshot` for small avatars (32-44px).

  5. Interaction demos that need interactivity: use inline <script> with the
     h() helper (see finite-mockup-no-innerhtml.rule). Avoid frameworks,
     avoid build steps — prototypes must run directly from the local server.

  6. Add a "what changed" notes block at the bottom of the mockup so design
     iterations are self-documenting when the user refreshes.
